Interface Enumeration<E>

All Known Implementing Classes:
AllPermissionCollection.SingletonEnumeration, ConcurrentHashMap.KeyIterator, ConcurrentHashMap.ValueIterator, EmptyEnumeration, Permissions.MetaEnumeration, StringTokenizer, TwoEnumerationsInOne
public interface Enumeration<E>

An Enumeration is used to sequence over a collection of objects.

Preferably an Iterator should be used. Iterator replaces the Enumeration interface and adds a way to remove elements from a collection.

Since:
Android 1.0
